Package: FDSC
Type: Package
Title: Functional Data Subgroup Clustering and Outlier Identification via Minimum Spanning Tree
Version: 1.0.0
Author: c(person("Chao", "Liu", , "liuc36@szu.edu.cn", role = c("aut", "cre")),
      person("Shimin", "Lin", , "2310125018@email.szu.edu.cn", role = "aut"),
      person("Jiaqi", "Li", , "ljq0814nana@gmail.com", role = "aut"))
Description: This package implements two functional data clustering algorithms based on
    minimum spanning tree (MST). FDSC-MST solves the subgroup clustering
    problem by constructing an MST using geographical distance and functional
    curve similarity, and applies subgroup pairwise penalties to MST edges. An alternating direction method of multipliers (ADMM) is
    utilized to solve the optimization problem. For contaminated data, this package implements FDSCOD-MST, 
    which simultaneously performs clustering and outlier detection.
